Survival Analysis of the OPTN/UNOS Data

Sehee Kim

Fan Wu

2016-07-05

Contents

  • Cross Tables for Dialysis Time x Diabetes Time (Onset)
  • Interaction between Dialysis Time and Diabetes Time
  • Interaction between Dialysis Time and Diabetes Onset
  • In this report, we consider the possible interaction between dialysis time and diabetes time (or age of diabetes onset). We exclude the patients with missing age of diabetes onset and/or missing diabetes type.
  • In the first section, we give some cross tables of graft failure rates for different combinations of dialysis time and diabetes time / age-of-onset.
  • In the second and third section, we give the relevant coefficient estimates from the stratified (by TX centers) Cox models.
  • Findings (diabetes time):
    • For graft failure, even main effects of diab duration (TDIABC) were not significant; for mortality, the main effects of TDIABC were significant.
    • For both endpoints, dialysis time itself is a stronger (dominating) risk factor; on the top of that, there may be no additional risk due to longer diab.
  • Findings (age of diabetes onset):
    • However, age of diabetes onset is a significant risk factor for graft failure.
    • No significant interactions with dialysis time existed, though.
